  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  older than 18 years (of both sexes)

          -  diagnosed with stable chronic heart failure NYHA class II-III

          -  ejection fraction &lt; 40 % as assessed by 2D echocardiography

          -  who have been optimized on Guideline Directed treatment for heart failure for at least
             a month prior to enrolling.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Known hypersensitivity to statin

          -  Treatment with statins during the past month prior to study.

          -  Serum creatinine &gt; 3 mg/dl

          -  Significant liver disease: liver enzymes 2.5 folds the upper normal limit

          -  Malignancy

          -  Pregnancy or lactation
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
